    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It's indeed a bug in the compiler. The current ABI encoder does not support passing structs from external calls, but it should show a proper error message.\r\n\r\nFor the moment, you can opt-in to the new encoder with `pragma experimental ABIEncoderV2;` or pass each individual struct member as separate arguments.",
